Submission from: ming.elen.utah.edu (128.110.18.208)
Submitted by: stjung


There is some weird thing about the order of multiple transition
occurrences of a signal.

For "examples/g/qr42.g "

   The order of the transitions of the signal 'a' is :
        a+/1 -> a-/2 -> a+/2 -> a-/1

   The orbits verification fails for this specification.

When I changed a-/2 to a-/1  and  a-/1   to a-/2 (the order becomes 
         a+/1 -> a-/1 -> a+/2 -> a-/2), the orbits verification succeeded.

For "examples/g/ebergen-all.g, ebegen-c.g, ebergen-b.g, ebegern-x.g, ebegen.g"

    It has same problem with qr42.g
    When the order is corrected, verification worked for all except
ebergen-all.g.
    

################################ modified qr42.g #########################
.name qr42
.inputs a d
.outputs b c x
#@.init_state [00000]
.graph
a+/2 c+
c+ b+/1 d+

b+/1 a-/2
a-/2 x+

d+ x+

x+ b-/1
b-/1 a+/1
a+/1 c-

c- b+/2 d-
b+/2 a-/1

d- x-

a-/1 x-
x- b-/2
b-/2 a+/2
.marking {<b-/2,a+/2>}
.end

############################### Modified ebegen-all.g ########################

.outputs a b c d x
#@.init_state [00000]
.graph
c+ b+/1 d+
b+/1 a-/2
d+ x+
a-/2 x+ 
x+ b-/1
b-/1 a+/1
a+/1 c-
c- b+/2 d-
b+/2 a-/1
d- x-
a-/1 x-
x- b-/2
b-/2 a+/2
a+/2 c+
.marking {<b-/2,a+/2>}
.end 
~

